# Trivy IaC ignore list. Each entry is a deliberate, documented starter default —
# not an oversight. Keeping them here (rather than loosening the scan severity)
# means Trivy still fails the build on any NEW high/critical misconfiguration.

# Public EKS API endpoint, reachable from 0.0.0.0/0.
# ON by default so you can run `kubectl`/Argo CD against the cluster with no
# bastion or VPN while evaluating this repo. Lock it down for real use by setting
# `cluster_endpoint_public_access = false` (or restricting the allowed CIDRs) in
# infra/environments/*/*.auto.tfvars.
AVD-AWS-0040
AWS-0040
AVD-AWS-0041
AWS-0041

# Unrestricted egress from the cluster security group.
# This is the Kubernetes norm — nodes must reach image registries, AWS APIs, etc.
# Constrain east-west/egress traffic with Kubernetes NetworkPolicies per workload
# rather than at the node security group.
AVD-AWS-0104
AWS-0104
